This month a number of Sieve extensions became published RFCs, along with an update to the Sieve base spec itself:

<ul>
	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5228">RFC 5228</a>]</strong> Sieve: An Email Filtering Language.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5229">RFC 5229</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Variables Extension.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5230">RFC 5230</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Vacation Extension.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5231">RFC 5231</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Relational Extension.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5232">RFC 5232</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Imap4flags Extension.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5233">RFC 5233</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Subaddress Extension.</li>

	<li><strong>[<a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5235">RFC 5235</a>]</strong> Sieve Email Filtering: Spamtest and Virustest Extensions.</li>
</ul>

Time for teh libSieve hacken!
